# Astro Development Guidelines

## Component Structure

- Use `.astro` extension for Astro components
- Place reusable components in [src/components/](mdc:src/components/)
- Organize components by feature (Header, Project, Ui, etc.)

## TypeScript

- Use TypeScript for scripts in [src/scripts/](mdc:src/scripts/)
- Define types in [src/types.ts](mdc:src/types.ts)
- Use strict TypeScript configuration from [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json)

## Styling

- Use Tailwind CSS classes for styling
- Component-specific styles go in [src/styles/components/](mdc:src/styles/components/)
- Global styles in [src/styles/global.css](mdc:src/styles/global.css)

## Content

- Store project data as MDX files in [src/content/projects/](mdc:src/content/projects/)
- Use [src/content/config.ts](mdc:src/content/config.ts) for content schema
- Follow the existing project structure for new content

## Scripts

- Interactive functionality in [src/scripts/](mdc:src/scripts/)
- Use vanilla JavaScript/TypeScript for client-side interactions
- Follow the existing patterns for navigation, preloader, and effects
